The paper deals with the complexity of branching programs, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also involves the analysis of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), as well as information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) due to the use of concepts such as amortization and submodular complexity measures. Finally, the paper touches on the broader field of computer science (cs.CS) as it provides insights into the limits of computation.
